race.description: Tabtouch Supports Pinjarra Park Racing Handicap
race.comment: MANJERI (5) jagged back to the tail of the field from a wide gate and failed to recover last start over this distance at Belmont. Has failed twice in a row in town over 1400m but bad gates haven't helped. Draws perfectly here and the claim brings him in nicely. Can bounce back. IMPRESSIVE JEWEL (6) was beaten a lip over today's journey at Belmont two back then struggled in a Listed race over the mile subsequently. Back in a far more suitable assignment today so a return to form is anticipated. MUDDY WATERS (1) has been freshened up since an eye-catching third over the mile at Pinjarra on 30 November. The winner of two from three at this trip. Right in contention. TRESPASSING (9) led and was only nailed close to home last start over this distance at Ascot. Fitter now and should be prominent for a long way. APPARATUS (3) is first-up from a two-month break and has transferred from the Hayes Team at Euroa to Dylan Bairstow. Goes well when fresh so watch the betting.
